data.text:
Constance M. “Frankie” Cole-Kobriger, age 32, of New Holstein, died on Friday, March 21, 2014. She was born June 29, 1981, daughter of Paul & Sheryl (Doxtator) Kobriger. Constance had attended Chilton High School, and worked at Tecumseh. She possessed a playful, childlike personality which was a blessing to both the young, and the young at heart. Constance was very family orientated and enjoyed time spent scrapbooking with her mother, and treasured being a loving mother to her boys, Braden & Brenner. Her magnificent inner and outer beauty will be missed by all those who knew her, and loved being around her. Survivors include her children: Braden & Brenner Cole; her fiancé: Brent Halda and his daughter: Brea Halda; her parents: Sheryl & Paul Kobriger; maternal grandparents: Marvin & Phyllis Doxtator; paternal grandparents: Jerome & JoAnne Kobriger; a brother: Craig Kobriger; a sister: Crystal (Steve) McCone; and aunts & uncles: Donna (Richard) Fluegge, Jack (Kathy) Doxtator, Colleen (Ken) Kurz, Rick Doxtator, Joan Doxtator, Joel Doxtator, Diane (Don) Kessler, Mike Kobriger, Joe (Roxanne) Kobriger, Bob (Terri) Kobriger, Barb (Jim) Pautz, Amy (Rick) Pethan, Tony (Tina) Kobriger, & Kate (Bill) Suttner. She is further survived by many cousins, other relatives, and friends. She was preceded in death by an aunt: Angie Doxtator. Funeral service will be at 7:00 pm on Tuesday, March 25, 2014 at the Wieting Family Funeral Home (411W. Main St.) in Chilton. Friends may call at the funeral home from 2:00 pm until 6:30 pm on Tuesday, March 25, 2014. Memorials given in the name of Constance M. “Frankie” Cole-Kobriger are greatly appreciated.
